---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About Badminton">
  <style>
    :root {
      --ab-navy:   #1B3A8F;
      --ab-ink:    #1a2d42;
      --ab-teal:   #0e7c7b;
      --ab-teallt: #13a8a7;
      --ab-gold:   #d4a840;
      --ab-cream:  #f0f4fb;
      --ab-white:  #ffffff;
      --ab-gray:   #6b7a8d;
      --ab-light:  #e2e8f4;
    }

    /* ── HERO ── */
    .ab-hero {
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0d1e4a 0%, #1B3A8F 55%, #1e4499 100%);
      color: #fff;
      min-height: 72vh;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      justify-content: center;
      position: relative;
      overflow: hidden;
      padding: 80px 40px 60px;
    }
    .ab-hero::before {
      content: '';
      position: absolute;
      inset: 0;
      background:
        radial-gradient(ellipse 70% 60% at 80% 50%, rgba(14,124,123,0.22) 0%, transparent 70%),
        radial-gradient(ellipse 50% 80% at 10% 80%, rgba(212,168,64,0.10) 0%, transparent 60%);
    }
    .ab-hero-inner {
      max-width: 860px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      position: relative;
      z-index: 1;
    }
    .ab-eyebrow {
      display: inline-block;
      font-weight: 600;
      font-size: 0.78rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.22em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--ab-gold);
      margin-bottom: 22px;
      border-left: 3px solid var(--ab-gold);
      padding-left: 12px;
    }
    .ab-hero h1 {
      font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', serif;
      font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 6vw, 4.6rem);
      line-height: 1.1;
      font-weight: 900;
      margin: 0 0 28px;
      letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    }
    .ab-hero h1 em {
      font-style: italic;
      color: var(--ab-teallt);
    }
    .ab-hero-lead {
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      color: rgba(255,255,255,0.8);
      max-width: 620px;
      line-height: 1.72;
      margin-bottom: 44px;
    }
    .ab-hero-stats {
      display: flex;
      gap: 48px;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
    }
    .ab-stat-item strong {
      display: block;
      font-family: Georgia, serif;
      font-size: 2.4rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: var(--ab-gold);
      line-height: 1;
    }
    .ab-stat-item span {
      font-size: 0.78rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: rgba(255,255,255,0.55);
      margin-top: 4px;
      display: block;
    }
    .ab-shuttlecock-bg {
      position: absolute;
      right: -60px;
      top: 50%;
      transform: translateY(-50%);
      font-size: 300px;
      opacity: 0.04;
      user-select: none;
      pointer-events: none;
      line-height: 1;
    }

    /* ── SECTION BASE ── */
    .ab-section {
      padding: 80px 40px;
    }
    .ab-section-inner {
      max-width: 860px;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }
    .ab-section-label {
      font-size: 0.75rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      letter-spacing: 0.22em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--ab-teal);
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }
    .ab-section h2 {
      font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', serif;
      font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4vw, 2.8rem);
      font-weight: 900;
      color: var(--ab-navy);
      line-height: 1.14;
      margin: 0 0 26px;
    }
    .ab-section h3 {
      font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', serif;
      font-size: 1.4rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: var(--ab-ink);
      margin: 36px 0 12px;
    }
    .ab-section p {
      margin-bottom: 18px;
      color: #2e3e50;
      line-height: 1.78;
    }
    .ab-section p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

    .ab-divider {
      width: 60px;
      height: 4px;
      background: linear-gradient(90deg, var(--ab-teal), var(--ab-gold));
      border-radius: 2px;
      margin-bottom: 34px;
    }
    .ab-divider-inv {
      background: linear-gradient(90deg, var(--ab-gold), var(--ab-teallt));
    }

    /* ── ORIGIN ── */
    .ab-origin { background: var(--ab-cream); }
    .ab-origin-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 60px;
      align-items: start;
    }
    .ab-timeline {
      border-left: 3px solid var(--ab-light);
      padding-left: 28px;
      margin-top: 8px;
    }
    .ab-tl-item {
      position: relative;
      margin-bottom: 30px;
    }
    .ab-tl-item::before {
      content: '';
      position: absolute;
      left: -34px;
      top: 6px;
      width: 12px;
      height: 12px;
      border-radius: 50%;
      background: var(--ab-teal);
      border: 3px solid var(--ab-cream);
      box-shadow: 0 0 0 2px var(--ab-teal);
    }
    .ab-tl-year {
      font-size: 0.72rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: 0.18em;
      color: var(--ab-gold);
      text-transform: uppercase;
      margin-bottom: 3px;
    }
    .ab-tl-text {
      font-size: 0.92rem;
      line-height: 1.6;
      color: #3a4d60;
      margin: 0;
    }

    /* ── OLYMPIC (dark) ── */
    .ab-olympic {
      background: #0d1e4a;
      color: #fff;
    }
    .ab-olympic .ab-section-label { color: var(--ab-gold); }
    .ab-olympic h2 { color: #fff; }
    .ab-olympic h3 { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9); }
    .ab-olympic p  { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.78); }

    .ab-disc-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(180px, 1fr));
      gap: 18px;
      margin-top: 38px;
    }
    .ab-disc-card {
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.06);
      border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1);
      border-radius: 12px;
      padding: 24px 20px;
      text-align: center;
      transition: background 0.25s, transform 0.25s;
    }
    .ab-disc-card:hover {
      background: rgba(14,124,123,0.28);
      transform: translateY(-4px);
    }
    .ab-disc-icon { font-size: 1.8rem; margin-bottom: 10px; }
    .ab-disc-card h4 {
      font-family: Georgia, serif;
      font-size: 1rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: #fff;
      margin: 0 0 6px;
    }
    .ab-disc-card p {
      font-size: 0.8rem;
      color: rgba(255,255,255,0.55);
      margin: 0;
    }
    .ab-blockquote {
      border-left: 4px solid var(--ab-gold);
      margin: 32px 0 0;
      padding: 16px 24px;
      background: rgba(212,168,64,0.08);
      border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;
    }
    .ab-blockquote p {
      font-family: Georgia, serif;
      font-style: italic;
      font-size: 1.08rem;
      color: rgba(255,255,255,0.85);
      margin: 0;
    }

    /* ── COMPETITIVE (white) ── */
    .ab-competitive { background: #fff; }

    .ab-fact-strip {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(180px, 1fr));
      border: 1px solid var(--ab-light);
      border-radius: 14px;
      overflow: hidden;
      margin: 40px 0;
    }
    .ab-fact-cell {
      padding: 28px 20px;
      border-right: 1px solid var(--ab-light);
      text-align: center;
    }
    .ab-fact-cell:last-child { border-right: none; }
    .ab-fact-num {
      font-family: Georgia, serif;
      font-size: 2.2rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: var(--ab-teal);
      line-height: 1;
      display: block;
    }
    .ab-fact-lbl {
      font-size: 0.75rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      letter-spacing: 0.1em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--ab-gray);
      margin-top: 6px;
      display: block;
    }
    .ab-competitive .ab-blockquote {
      background: rgba(14,124,123,0.06);
    }
    .ab-competitive .ab-blockquote p {
      color: var(--ab-ink);
    }

    /* ── INTERNATIONAL (cream) ── */
    .ab-international { background: var(--ab-cream); }

    .ab-tournament-list {
      list-style: none;
      padding: 0;
      margin: 24px 0 0;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 14px;
    }
    .ab-tournament-list li {
      display: flex;
      align-items: flex-start;
      gap: 16px;
      padding: 18px 22px;
      background: #fff;
      border-radius: 10px;
      border-left: 4px solid var(--ab-teal);
    }
    .ab-t-icon { font-size: 1.4rem; flex-shrink: 0; margin-top: 1px; }
    .ab-t-name {
      font-weight: 600;
      font-size: 0.96rem;
      color: var(--ab-navy);
      display: block;
      margin-bottom: 2px;
    }
    .ab-t-desc {
      font-size: 0.85rem;
      color: var(--ab-gray);
      margin: 0;
      line-height: 1.55;
    }

    /* ── USA (white) ── */
    .ab-usa { background: #fff; }

    .ab-player-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(230px, 1fr));
      gap: 20px;
      margin-top: 36px;
    }
    .ab-player-card {
      background: var(--ab-cream);
      border-radius: 14px;
      padding: 26px 22px;
      border-top: 4px solid var(--ab-gold);
      transition: box-shadow 0.25s, transform 0.25s;
    }
    .ab-player-card:hover {
      box-shadow: 0 12px 36px rgba(27,58,143,0.13);
      transform: translateY(-3px);
    }
    .ab-player-tags {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: 6px;
      margin: 10px 0 12px;
    }
    .ab-player-tag {
      display: inline-block;
      padding: 4px 10px;
      background: rgba(14,124,123,0.1);
      border: 1px solid rgba(14,124,123,0.3);
      border-radius: 100px;
      font-size: 0.72rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: var(--ab-teal);
      letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    }
    .ab-player-flag { font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 8px; }
    .ab-player-name {
      font-family: Georgia, serif;
      font-size: 1.15rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: var(--ab-navy);
      margin: 0 0 3px;
    }
    .ab-player-role {
      font-size: 0.73rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      letter-spacing: 0.1em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--ab-teal);
      margin-bottom: 10px;
      display: block;
    }
    .ab-player-bio {
      font-size: 0.86rem;
      line-height: 1.6;
      color: #4a5a6a;
      margin: 0;
    }

    /* ── PAN AM (dark) ── */
    .ab-panam {
      background: #0d1e4a;
      color: #fff;
    }
    .ab-panam .ab-section-label { color: var(--ab-gold); }
    .ab-panam h2 { color: #fff; }
    .ab-panam h3 { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9); }
    .ab-panam p  { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.78); }

    .ab-badge-row {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: 10px;
      margin: 20px 0 30px;
    }
    .ab-badge {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 6px;
      padding: 7px 14px;
      background: rgba(14,124,123,0.25);
      border: 1px solid rgba(19,168,167,0.4);
      border-radius: 100px;
      font-size: 0.8rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: var(--ab-teallt);
      letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    }

    /* ── MASSACHUSETTS (cream) ── */
    .ab-massachusetts { background: var(--ab-cream); }

    .ab-wayside-box {
      background: #fff;
      border-radius: 16px;
      padding: 44px 40px;
      border: 1px solid #d8e2f0;
      box-shadow: 0 6px 28px rgba(27,58,143,0.08);
      margin-top: 36px;
      position: relative;
      overflow: hidden;
    }
    .ab-wayside-box::before {
      content: '🏸';
      position: absolute;
      right: 28px;
      top: 28px;
      font-size: 68px;
      opacity: 0.06;
    }
    .ab-wayside-box h3 {
      font-family: Georgia, serif;
      font-size: 1.6rem;
      color: var(--ab-navy);
      margin: 0 0 4px;
    }
    .ab-wayside-tagline {
      font-size: 0.78rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      letter-spacing: 0.14em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--ab-teal);
      margin-bottom: 16px;
      display: block;
    }
    .ab-wayside-box p { margin-bottom: 16px; color: #2e3e50; line-height: 1.78; }
    .ab-wayside-box a.ab-cta-link {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 8px;
      background: var(--ab-teal);
      color: #fff;
      padding: 13px 26px;
      border-radius: 8px;
      text-decoration: none;
      font-weight: 600;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.04em;
      transition: background 0.2s, transform 0.15s;
      margin-top: 6px;
    }
    .ab-wayside-box a.ab-cta-link:hover {
      background: #0d6e6d;
      transform: translateY(-2px);
    }
    .ab-coach-strip {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: 14px;
      margin-top: 26px;
    }
    .ab-coach-tag {
      background: var(--ab-cream);
      border-radius: 8px;
      padding: 13px 16px;
      border-left: 3px solid var(--ab-gold);
      flex: 1;
      min-width: 200px;
    }
    .ab-coach-tag strong {
      display: block;
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      color: var(--ab-navy);
      margin-bottom: 2px;
    }
    .ab-coach-tag small {
      font-size: 0.8rem;
      color: var(--ab-gray);
    }

    /* ── RESPONSIVE ── */
    @media (max-width: 700px) {
      .ab-hero { padding: 56px 22px 44px; min-height: 60vh; }
      .ab-section { padding: 60px 22px; }
      .ab-origin-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 32px; }
      .ab-hero-stats { gap: 24px; }
      .ab-wayside-box { padding: 26px 20px; }
      .ab-fact-cell { border-right: none; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--ab-light); }
      .ab-fact-cell:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
      .ab-closing { padding: 64px 22px; }
    }
  </style>

  <!-- ── HERO ── -->
  <section class="ab-hero">
    <div class="ab-shuttlecock-bg">🏸</div>
    <div class="ab-hero-inner">
      <span class="ab-eyebrow">Massachusetts Badminton Foundation</span>
      <h1>The Sport<br>the World <em>Already</em><br>Loves — and<br>America is<br>Discovering</h1>
      <p class="ab-hero-lead">
        From a British army officer's garden party to the center stage of the Olympic Games — badminton is one of the fastest, most athletic, and most watched sports on the planet. Here is everything you need to know.
      </p>
      <div class="ab-hero-stats">
        <div class="ab-stat-item">
          <strong>220+</strong>
          <span>Member nations<br>in the BWF</span>
        </div>
        <div class="ab-stat-item">
          <strong>1992</strong>
          <span>Olympic debut<br>Barcelona</span>
        </div>
        <div class="ab-stat-item">
          <strong>300 mph</strong>
          <span>Top shuttlecock<br>recorded speed</span>
        </div>
        <div class="ab-stat-item">
          <strong>5</strong>
          <span>Olympic gold<br>disciplines</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── ORIGINS ── -->
  <section id="origin" class="ab-section ab-origin">
    <div class="ab-section-inner">
      <div class="ab-origin-grid">
        <div>
          <p class="ab-section-label">Where It All Began</p>
          <h2>A 2,000-Year Journey to the Olympic Stage</h2>
          <div class="ab-divider"></div>
          <p>
            Long before there were carbon-fiber rackets and dedicated training academies, children across ancient Greece, India, China, and Japan were hitting a shuttlecock — a small cork base threaded with feathers — back and forth with wooden paddles. That simple, joyful act is the seed from which the modern sport of badminton grew.
          </p>
          <p>
            The game we recognize today took formal shape in the mid-19th century in England. British Army officers stationed in British India encountered a game called <em>Poona</em> — named after the city of Pune — in which players batted a feathered cork across a makeshift net. They brought it home, and in 1873, the Duke of Beaufort introduced it at his country estate called Badminton House in Gloucestershire. The name stuck.
          </p>
          <p>
            The newly named sport spread rapidly. The Badminton Association of England published the first official set of rules in 1893, and competitive play quickly grew beyond British borders, traveling along trade and colonial routes to Southeast Asia — where it would find its greatest devotees and eventually its most dominant champions.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="ab-section-label">Timeline</p>
          <div class="ab-timeline">
            <div class="ab-tl-item">
              <p class="ab-tl-year">~200 BC</p>
              <p class="ab-tl-text">Shuttlecock games documented in ancient China, Greece, and India — forerunners of modern badminton.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="ab-tl-item">
              <p class="ab-tl-year">1860s</p>
              <p class="ab-tl-text">British officers in India encounter Poona, a net-based shuttlecock game, and bring it to England.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="ab-tl-item">
              <p class="ab-tl-year">1873</p>
              <p class="ab-tl-text">The Duke of Beaufort introduces the game at Badminton House — and the sport gets its enduring name.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="ab-tl-item">
              <p class="ab-tl-year">1893</p>
              <p class="ab-tl-text">Badminton Association of England formalizes the rules. Competitive play begins.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="ab-tl-item">
              <p class="ab-tl-year">1934</p>
              <p class="ab-tl-text">The Badminton World Federation (BWF) — originally the IBF — is founded with 9 member nations.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="ab-tl-item">
              <p class="ab-tl-year">1948</p>
              <p class="ab-tl-text">The prestigious Thomas Cup — the "Badminton World Cup" — is played for the first time.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="ab-tl-item">
              <p class="ab-tl-year">1992</p>
              <p class="ab-tl-text">Badminton makes its Olympic debut at the Barcelona Games with four events.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="ab-tl-item">
              <p class="ab-tl-year">1996</p>
              <p class="ab-tl-text">Mixed doubles added at Atlanta, completing the five Olympic disciplines still contested today.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="ab-tl-item">
              <p class="ab-tl-year">Today</p>
              <p class="ab-tl-text">The BWF has over 220 member nations — more than FIFA. Badminton is the world's second most participated racket sport.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── OLYMPICS ── -->
  <section id="olympic" class="ab-section ab-olympic">
    <div class="ab-section-inner">
      <p class="ab-section-label">The Biggest Stage</p>
      <h2>An Olympic Sport Since 1992 — and a Fiercely Contested One</h2>
      <div class="ab-divider ab-divider-inv"></div>
      <p>
        Many people are surprised to learn that badminton has been a full Olympic medal sport for over three decades. Since its debut at the Barcelona 1992 Summer Games, it has grown into one of the most watched events at every Olympiad — particularly across Asia, where television audiences rival those of soccer and basketball.
      </p>
      <p>
        Five separate disciplines are contested at every Summer Olympics, meaning ten sets of Olympic medals are awarded in badminton alone. That breadth reflects the sport's versatility — it rewards explosive power, delicate touch, tactical intelligence, physical stamina, and lightning-fast reflexes, often within the same rally.
      </p>
      <div class="ab-disc-grid">
        <div class="ab-disc-card">
          <div class="ab-disc-icon">🏸</div>
          <h4>Men's Singles</h4>
          <p>One-on-one combat at its most intense — raw speed and tactical mastery.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ab-disc-card">
          <div class="ab-disc-icon">🏸</div>
          <h4>Women's Singles</h4>
          <p>Widely regarded as some of the most technically refined matches in the sport.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ab-disc-card">
          <div class="ab-disc-icon">🏸</div>
          <h4>Men's Doubles</h4>
          <p>Partnership, coordination, and the fastest exchanges in badminton.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ab-disc-card">
          <div class="ab-disc-icon">🏸</div>
          <h4>Women's Doubles</h4>
          <p>A discipline that showcases extraordinary court coverage and teamwork.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ab-disc-card">
          <div class="ab-disc-icon">🏸</div>
          <h4>Mixed Doubles</h4>
          <p>Added in Atlanta 1996 — dynamic, strategic, and endlessly unpredictable.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="ab-blockquote" style="margin-top:44px;">
        <p>"No other sport combines the aerobic demand of distance running with the explosive power of sprinting, the hand-eye precision of table tennis, and the court intelligence of chess — all at the same time." — Often cited by sports scientists studying badminton athletes.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── THE SPORT ── -->
  <section id="competitive" class="ab-section ab-competitive">
    <div class="ab-section-inner">
      <p class="ab-section-label">Understanding the Game</p>
      <h2>Not a Backyard Game. One of the Most Demanding Sports on Earth.</h2>
      <div class="ab-divider"></div>
      <p>
        Here is a fact that stops most people cold: the shuttlecock in professional badminton has been recorded traveling over 300 miles per hour off a smash — making it the fastest-moving object in any racket sport, faster than a tennis serve, faster than a squash ball, faster than a golf drive off the tee. A player has roughly 130 milliseconds to react. That is less than the time it takes to blink.
      </p>
      <div class="ab-fact-strip">
        <div class="ab-fact-cell">
          <span class="ab-fact-num">300+</span>
          <span class="ab-fact-lbl">mph smash speed</span>
        </div>
        <div class="ab-fact-cell">
          <span class="ab-fact-num">6 km</span>
          <span class="ab-fact-lbl">average distance<br>covered per match</span>
        </div>
        <div class="ab-fact-cell">
          <span class="ab-fact-num">1000+</span>
          <span class="ab-fact-lbl">direction changes<br>per match</span>
        </div>
        <div class="ab-fact-cell">
          <span class="ab-fact-num">21</span>
          <span class="ab-fact-lbl">points to win<br>a game (best of 3)</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p>
        A professional badminton player covers an average of 6 kilometers per match, changes direction over 1,000 times, and performs explosive lunges to all corners of the court — a discipline so physically punishing that top players train alongside sprinters, gymnasts, and martial artists to develop the right blend of fitness.
      </p>
      <h3>How a Match Works</h3>
      <p>
        Matches are best-of-three games. Each game is played to 21 points, with a two-point lead required to win. At 20-all, play continues until one player or pair leads by two. If the score reaches 29-all, the next point wins. Serves alternate sides, and a rally — not just the server — wins the point under the modern rally-point scoring system introduced in 2006.
      </p>
      <h3>Strategy and Skill</h3>
      <p>
        Badminton is as much a mental game as a physical one. Players use an array of shots — clears, drops, net shots, lifts, drives, and the devastating smash — to maneuver opponents out of position. At the elite level, deception is as valuable as power: a slight flick of the wrist can send the shuttle in an entirely different direction from where the opponent expects it, creating openings in a fraction of a second.
      </p>
      <p>
        Doubles play adds a layer of tactical complexity. Pairs must communicate constantly, rotating between a front-and-back formation for attacking play and a side-by-side defensive structure, seamlessly shifting in real time. The synchronized movement of a well-trained doubles pair is something to behold — equal parts athletic performance and choreographed precision.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── WORLD STAGE ── -->
  <section id="international" class="ab-section ab-international">
    <div class="ab-section-inner">
      <p class="ab-section-label">The World Stage</p>
      <h2>A Global Sport with a Fiercely Competitive Circuit</h2>
      <div class="ab-divider"></div>
      <p>
        Beyond the Olympics, badminton is governed by the Badminton World Federation (BWF), which oversees a full-season international circuit and several historic team competitions that rival any championship in sport for prestige and passion.
      </p>
      <ul class="ab-tournament-list">
        <li>
          <span class="ab-t-icon">🌍</span>
          <div>
            <span class="ab-t-name">BWF World Championships</span>
            <p class="ab-t-desc">The sport's individual world title, held annually. Nations compete to crown the world's best in all five disciplines. A BWF World Championship gold is considered second only to an Olympic gold in prestige.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="ab-t-icon">🏆</span>
          <div>
            <span class="ab-t-name">Thomas Cup (Men's Team) &amp; Uber Cup (Women's Team)</span>
            <p class="ab-t-desc">The oldest and most storied team competitions in the sport. First held in 1948 and 1957 respectively, they bring nations together every two years in a format that blends individual excellence with national pride.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="ab-t-icon">🎯</span>
          <div>
            <span class="ab-t-name">Sudirman Cup (Mixed Team)</span>
            <p class="ab-t-desc">Launched in 1989, this biennial mixed-team event contests all five disciplines under one roof. Only a nation with well-rounded strength across every category can win.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="ab-t-icon">⭐</span>
          <div>
            <span class="ab-t-name">BWF World Tour — Super 1000 through Super 100</span>
            <p class="ab-t-desc">A tiered season-long circuit spanning every continent, culminating in the World Tour Finals. The higher the level, the greater the ranking points and prize money — and the higher the intensity of competition.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="ab-t-icon">🌎</span>
          <div>
            <span class="ab-t-name">Pan American Badminton Championships</span>
            <p class="ab-t-desc">The premier multi-disciplinary championship for the Americas, bringing together nations from North, Central, and South America. For U.S. players, this is the proving ground where continental rankings are earned and Olympic pathways are built.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="ab-t-icon">🎖️</span>
          <div>
            <span class="ab-t-name">Pan American Games</span>
            <p class="ab-t-desc">Badminton has been a fixture of the Pan American Games since 1955. These multi-sport games, held every four years between Summer Olympics, are the Western Hemisphere's most prestigious athletic gathering — and badminton earns its rightful place among the flagship events.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── USA & PLAYERS ── -->
  <section id="usa" class="ab-section ab-usa">
    <div class="ab-section-inner">
      <p class="ab-section-label">The American Story</p>
      <h2>The United States: A Growing Force in a Global Game</h2>
      <div class="ab-divider"></div>
      <p>
        Badminton in the United States has a longer competitive history than most people realize. USA Badminton (USAB), the national governing body, has existed since the 1930s and has been sending athletes to international competitions — including the Olympics — for decades. What is changing now is the scale and ambition of American badminton.
      </p>
      <p>
        For much of the latter 20th century, Asian nations — China, Indonesia, South Korea, Malaysia, Japan — dominated the international circuit to such a degree that it was difficult for other countries to break through. But that era of total dominance has been gradually shifting, and the United States has been among the countries building a genuine competitive pipeline at both the junior and senior levels.
      </p>
      <p>
        The rise of immigrant communities from badminton-loving nations has been one of the most significant drivers of American badminton's growth. Cities with large Southeast Asian, South Asian, East Asian, and South American communities have become hotbeds of grassroots badminton — producing clubs, leagues, and young players who represent a new generation of American talent.
      </p>
      <h3>American Players Who Represented the USA on the World Stage</h3>
